  "prompt": "What are your top 10 favorite songs of all time? Why?",
  "response": "As an AI, I don't have personal preferences, emotions, or experiences, so I don't have favorite songs. However, I can share a list of popular and critically acclaimed songs that many people and critics often regard highly. Here are ten songs that are frequently mentioned as some of the all-time greats:\n\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen** - Known for its innovative structure, blending rock, opera, and ballad. It's a timeless classic with powerful vocals and intricate musical composition.\n2. **\"Imagine\" by John Lennon** - This song is cherished for its hopeful message of peace and unity, and Lennon's soulful performance.\n3. **\"Stairway to Heaven\" by Led Zeppelin** - Famous for its gradual build-up and epic guitar solo, it's often considered one of the greatest rock songs ever.\n4. **\"Hey Jude\" by The Beatles** - Loved for its catchy melody and uplifting message, it's a standout in The Beatles' legendary catalog.\n5. **\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" by Nirvana** - This track became an anthem for a generation and defined the grunge movement in the 1990s.\n6. **\"Hotel California\" by Eagles** - Known for its haunting lyrics and iconic guitar solos, it's a staple of classic rock.\n7. **\"Like a Rolling Stone\" by Bob Dylan** - This song revolutionized rock and roll with its introspective and vivid storytelling.\n8. **\"Billie Jean\" by Michael Jackson** - With its infectious beat and groundbreaking music video, it remains one of the most iconic pop songs ever.\n9. **\"Purple Rain\" by Prince** - Celebrated for its emotional depth and powerful guitar work, this song showcases Prince's versatility as an artist.\n10. **\"Hallelujah\" by Leonard Cohen** - Revered for its beautiful melody and profound lyrics, it has been covered by countless artists and remains a deeply moving piece.\n\nThese songs have had a significant impact on music and culture, resonating with audiences across different generations and continuing to be celebrated for their craftsmanship and emotional power.",
